      "summary": "Broadcast auth wrapper functions discard meaningful errors, so callers cannot observe publish failures through the abstraction.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
        "goseg/auth/auth.go",
        "goseg/leak/broadcast.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`broadcastAuth` invokes the auth manager broadcast call but immediately returns `nil` instead of the call result.",
        "`UnauthBroadcast` also always returns `nil`, while the public `BroadcastToClients` surface still presents an `error`-returning API.",
        "`leak/broadcast.go` and other producers rely on the broadcast interface and receive false-positive success from `BroadcastToClients` even when downstream publish fails.",
        "The seam is intended to isolate callers from manager specifics, but it silently violates its own interface contract."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Thread the underlying publish result through all adapter functions (`broadcastAuth`, `UnauthBroadcast`, and any wrapper call sites), and add tests that assert failures are propagated from `auth.GetClientManager().BroadcastAuth/Broadcast` through `BroadcastToClients` and callers.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "adapter_contract_erosion"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "schedulebus_sync_block",
      "summary": "Synchronous schedule-event channel publishing leaks backpressure into workflow control paths instead of acting as an async abstraction seam.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "The schedule event channel is created as an unbuffered channel and published via a direct send in `PublishSchedulePack`.",
        "`SchedulePackEvents` returns a receive channel but there is no non-blocking publish path or buffering in the sender.",
        "Synchronous send semantics in `PublishSchedulePack` can stall callers in workflow code paths that trigger scheduling events without active listeners."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Keep the abstraction boundary by turning publishing into non-blocking or buffered semantics (bounded channel + drop/drop-oldest policy), or queue events in an internal dispatcher goroutine so control-plane calls cannot block on observer availability.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "event_bus_sync_contract"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "config_patch_fragmentation",
      "summary": "Config update abstraction is fragmented across repeated field-by-field methods, making option evolution error-prone and low-cohesion.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/config/config.go",
        "goseg/structs/configs.go",
        "goseg/defaults/version.go",
        "goseg/defaults/defaults.go"
